wfOsiDelete.name: wfOsiDelete
wfOsiDelete.description: This value determines whether OSI is configured on this slot.

wfOsiDisable.name: wfOsiDisable
wfOsiDisable.description: This value determines whether OSI is to startup.

wfOsiState.name: wfOsiState
wfOsiState.description: This value determines whether OSI is to startup.

wfOsiIsisVersion.name: wfOsiIsisVersion
wfOsiIsisVersion.description: This read-only parameter identifies the version number of the IS-IS protocol to which this node conforms to.

wfOsiRouterType.name: wfOsiRouterType
wfOsiRouterType.description: This value determines whether this system is an L1-only router or L1-L2 IS.

wfOsiRouterId.name: wfOsiRouterId
wfOsiRouterId.description: This value contains the system ID of this Intermediate System. If no value is entered by the user, Site Manager should supply a 6-byte value that will be unique (a MAC address would work).

wfOsiLoadBal.name: wfOsiLoadBal
wfOsiLoadBal.description: This Boolean defines whether or not we are doing load balancing over multiple paths.

wfOsiMaxAreas.name: wfOsiMaxAreas
wfOsiMaxAreas.description: This value defines the maximum allowable number of areas addresses for the domain that this router exists in.

wfOsiMaxEs.name: wfOsiMaxEs
wfOsiMaxEs.description: This value defines the maximum allowable number of End Systems for the area that this router exists in.

wfOsiMaxL1Is.name: wfOsiMaxL1Is
wfOsiMaxL1Is.description: This value defines the maximum allowable number of L1 Intermediate Systems for the area that this router exists in.

wfOsiMaxL2Is.name: wfOsiMaxL2Is
wfOsiMaxL2Is.description: This value defines the maximum allowable number of L2 Intermediate Systems for the domain that this router exists in.

wfOsiMaxExtAddr.name: wfOsiMaxExtAddr
wfOsiMaxExtAddr.description: This value defines the maximum allowable number of External Addresses for the domain that this router exists in. The default value of this field is 0.

wfOsiCksumIsPdus.name: wfOsiCksumIsPdus
wfOsiCksumIsPdus.description: This value indicates whether ISIS PDUs will carry a checksum.

wfOsiL1LspPassword.name: wfOsiL1LspPassword
wfOsiL1LspPassword.description: This assigns a password such that only L1 Lsps with the matching password will be accepted. All L1 Lsps generated by this system will contain this string in the password option.

wfOsiL2LspPassword.name: wfOsiL2LspPassword
wfOsiL2LspPassword.description: This assigns a password such that only L2 Lsps with the matching password will be accepted. All L2 Lsps generated by this system will contain this string in the password option.

wfOsiAreaAddr.name: wfOsiAreaAddr
wfOsiAreaAddr.description: This Assigns the area address for this router. This field must be filled in. If the user doesn't enter a value, then assign 490040. Site Manager must force the user to enter at least a 3-byte value for this field.

wfOsiAreaAddrAlias1.name: wfOsiAreaAddrAlias1
wfOsiAreaAddrAlias1.description: This Assigns the first area address alias for this router. This field does no have to be filled in, but if the user tries to enter a value, Site Manager must make sure that it is at least 3-bytes in length.

wfOsiAreaAddrAlias2.name: wfOsiAreaAddrAlias2
wfOsiAreaAddrAlias2.description: This Assigns the second area address alias for this router. This field does no have to be filled in, but if the user tries to enter a value, Site Manager must make sure that it is at least 3-bytes in length.

wfOsiL1LspDbOverloads.name: wfOsiL1LspDbOverloads
wfOsiL1LspDbOverloads.description: Number of times the L1 Lsp Database Overload event has been generated.

wfOsiL2LspDbOverloads.name: wfOsiL2LspDbOverloads
wfOsiL2LspDbOverloads.description: Number of times the L2 Lsp Database Overload event has been generated.

wfOsiManAddrDroppedAreas.name: wfOsiManAddrDroppedAreas
wfOsiManAddrDroppedAreas.description: Number of times the Manual Address Dropped from Area event has been generated.

wfOsiSeqNumberSkips.name: wfOsiSeqNumberSkips
wfOsiSeqNumberSkips.description: Number of times the Sequence Number Skipped event has been generated.

wfOsiOwnLspPurges.name: wfOsiOwnLspPurges
wfOsiOwnLspPurges.description: Number of times the Own Lsp Purged event has been generated.

wfOsiOthLspPurges.name: wfOsiOthLspPurges
wfOsiOthLspPurges.description: Number of times the Other Lsp Purged event has been generated.

wfOsiExceedMaxSeqNums.name: wfOsiExceedMaxSeqNums
wfOsiExceedMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the Attempt tp Exceed Maximum Sequence Number event has been generated.

wfOsiNearestL2Is.name: wfOsiNearestL2Is
wfOsiNearestL2Is.description: This is the ID of the Nearest L2 system in this area.

wfOsiMaxDynEs.name: wfOsiMaxDynEs
wfOsiMaxDynEs.description: This is the maximum number of dynamically learned (via Hello) End Systems allowed per slot.

wfOsiMaxDynL1Is.name: wfOsiMaxDynL1Is
wfOsiMaxDynL1Is.description: This is the maximum number of dynamically learned (via Hello) Level 1 Intermediate Systems allowed per slot.

wfOsiMaxDynL2Is.name: wfOsiMaxDynL2Is
wfOsiMaxDynL2Is.description: This is the maximum number of dynamically learned (via Hello) Level 2 Intermediate Systems allowed per slot.

wfOsiNumDynEsAdjs.name: wfOsiNumDynEsAdjs
wfOsiNumDynEsAdjs.description: Number of Dynamic ES adjs the osi master gate receives from the cct gate.

wfOsiNumDynL1Adjs.name: wfOsiNumDynL1Adjs
wfOsiNumDynL1Adjs.description: Number of Dynamic L1 adjs the osi master gate receives from the cct gate.

wfOsiNumDynL2Adjs.name: wfOsiNumDynL2Adjs
wfOsiNumDynL2Adjs.description: Number of Dynamic L2 adjs the osi master gate receives from the cct gate.

wfOsiNumDynPtpEsAdjs.name: wfOsiNumDynPtpEsAdjs
wfOsiNumDynPtpEsAdjs.description: Number of Dynamic Point-to-Point ES adjs the osi master gate receives on.

wfOsiNumDynPtpIsAdjs.name: wfOsiNumDynPtpIsAdjs
wfOsiNumDynPtpIsAdjs.description: Number of Dynamic Point-to-Point IS adjs the osi master gate receives on .

wfOsiClnpSrcRtOptionDisable.name: wfOsiClnpSrcRtOptionDisable
wfOsiClnpSrcRtOptionDisable.description: Enable/Disable processing of Source Route options in CLNP PDUs. This is required for GOSIP v2 support. GOSIP prohibits processing Source Routing options.

wfOsiNumL1Lsps.name: wfOsiNumL1Lsps
wfOsiNumL1Lsps.description: Number of L1 LSPs stored in database.

wfOsiNumL2Lsps.name: wfOsiNumL2Lsps
wfOsiNumL2Lsps.description: Number of L2 LSPs stored in database.

wfOsiFletchRelaxedEnable.name: wfOsiFletchRelaxedEnable
wfOsiFletchRelaxedEnable.description: Enable/Disable whether non-standard Fletcher Checksums are allowed in LSP's. If enabled, a log message will be generated, otherwise the LSP will be rejected.

wfOsiStaticRouteTable.name: wfOsiStaticRouteTable
wfOsiStaticRouteTable.description: This table contains all the static routes for this system.

wfOsiStaticRouteEntry.name: wfOsiStaticRouteEntry
wfOsiStaticRouteEntry.description: This is the Static Route Entry for the Static Route Table.

wfOsiStaticRouteDelete.name: wfOsiStaticRouteDelete
wfOsiStaticRouteDelete.description: Create/Delete parameter for Osi Static Route Record.

wfOsiStaticRouteDisable.name: wfOsiStaticRouteDisable
wfOsiStaticRouteDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter for this Static Route.

wfOsiStaticRouteAddr.name: wfOsiStaticRouteAddr
wfOsiStaticRouteAddr.description: This specifies the address of the static route. It is also the inst_id.

wfOsiStaticRouteNibbleLength.name: wfOsiStaticRouteNibbleLength
wfOsiStaticRouteNibbleLength.description: This is the length in nibbles of the static route address. It is necessary to specify it in nibbles since the static route may be an external address which can be specified in nibbles.

wfOsiStaticRouteNextHopIs.name: wfOsiStaticRouteNextHopIs
wfOsiStaticRouteNextHopIs.description: This is the 6-octet ID of the next Hop IS that all data destined to wfOsiStaticRouteAddr will be forwarded to.

wfOsiStaticRouteType.name: wfOsiStaticRouteType
wfOsiStaticRouteType.description: This specifies whether the destination is an End System, an area, or an external Domain.

wfOsiStaticRouteCost.name: wfOsiStaticRouteCost
wfOsiStaticRouteCost.description: This value is the cost to get to this address.

wfOsiCircuitTable.name: wfOsiCircuitTable
wfOsiCircuitTable.description: This Table contains all circuit configuration info counters available on a per circuit basis.

wfOsiCircuitEntry.name: wfOsiCircuitEntry
wfOsiCircuitEntry.description: This is the circuit entry record that appears in the Circuit Table.

wfOsiCircuitDelete.name: wfOsiCircuitDelete
wfOsiCircuitDelete.description: This value determines whether this circuit is configured.

wfOsiCircuitState.name: wfOsiCircuitState
wfOsiCircuitState.description: This indicates whether the circuit state is up or down.

wfOsiCircuitId.name: wfOsiCircuitId
wfOsiCircuitId.description: A unique value for each known circuit.

wfOsiCircuitRouterLevel.name: wfOsiCircuitRouterLevel
wfOsiCircuitRouterLevel.description: This is the level protocol that the circuit runs. Its a bit mask to allow for some combination of L1, L2, External, ES-IS-only.

wfOsiCircuitL1DefaultMetric.name: wfOsiCircuitL1DefaultMetric
wfOsiCircuitL1DefaultMetric.description: This is the default cost of using this circuit for L1 traffic.

wfOsiCircuitL2DefaultMetric.name: wfOsiCircuitL2DefaultMetric
wfOsiCircuitL2DefaultMetric.description: This is the default cost of using this circuit for L2 traffic.

wfOsiCircuitL1DrPriority.name: wfOsiCircuitL1DrPriority
wfOsiCircuitL1DrPriority.description: This is the priority for this system to become L1 designated router on this LAN circuit.

wfOsiCircuitL2DrPriority.name: wfOsiCircuitL2DrPriority
wfOsiCircuitL2DrPriority.description: This is the priority for this system to become L2 designated router on this LAN circuit.

wfOsiCircuitIsisHelloTimer.name: wfOsiCircuitIsisHelloTimer
wfOsiCircuitIsisHelloTimer.description: This is the period (secs) between IIH hello transmissions.

wfOsiCircuitEsisHelloTimer.name: wfOsiCircuitEsisHelloTimer
wfOsiCircuitEsisHelloTimer.description: This is the period (secs) between ISH hello transmissions.

wfOsiCircuitEshConfigTime.name: wfOsiCircuitEshConfigTime
wfOsiCircuitEshConfigTime.description: This is the suggested time between ESH transmissions from an ES went in ISHs (ESCT).

wfOsiCircuitPassword.name: wfOsiCircuitPassword
wfOsiCircuitPassword.description: This is Circuit Password for this circuit. Used to filter out Hellos from systems without the correct password.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedPkts.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedPkts
wfOsiCircuitReceivedPkts.description: This is the number of pkts that have been received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitSentPkts.name: wfOsiCircuitSentPkts
wfOsiCircuitSentPkts.description: This is the number of pkts sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitDroppedPkts.name: wfOsiCircuitDroppedPkts
wfOsiCircuitDroppedPkts.description: This is the number of pkts dropped on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitFragmentedPdus.name: wfOsiCircuitFragmentedPdus
wfOsiCircuitFragmentedPdus.description: This is the number of pdus that had to be fragmented when forwarded out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitCongestionDiscards.name: wfOsiCircuitCongestionDiscards
wfOsiCircuitCongestionDiscards.description: This is the number of PDUs dropped because of congestion.

wfOsiCircuitAddrUnreachDiscards.name: wfOsiCircuitAddrUnreachDiscards
wfOsiCircuitAddrUnreachDiscards.description: This is the number of PDUs dropped because the destination is unreachable.

wfOsiCircuitAgedPduDiscards.name: wfOsiCircuitAgedPduDiscards
wfOsiCircuitAgedPduDiscards.description: This is the number of PDUs dropped because of aging.

wfOsiCircuitPduFormatErrDiscards.name: wfOsiCircuitPduFormatErrDiscards
wfOsiCircuitPduFormatErrDiscards.description: This is the number of PDUs dropped because of Format Error.

wfOsiCircuitUnsuppOptsDiscards.name: wfOsiCircuitUnsuppOptsDiscards
wfOsiCircuitUnsuppOptsDiscards.description: This is the number of PDUs dropped because they contain unsupported options.

wfOsiCircuitSentErrorReports.name: wfOsiCircuitSentErrorReports
wfOsiCircuitSentErrorReports.description: This is the number of error reports sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedControlPdus.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedControlPdus
wfOsiCircuitReceivedControlPdus.description: This is the number of ESIS or ISIS PDUs received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitSentControlPdus.name: wfOsiCircuitSentControlPdus
wfOsiCircuitSentControlPdus.description: This is the number of ESIS or ISIS PDUs sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitStateChanges.name: wfOsiCircuitStateChanges
wfOsiCircuitStateChanges.description: This is the number of times the circuit goes from down to up or from up to down.

wfOsiCircuitAdjStateChanges.name: wfOsiCircuitAdjStateChanges
wfOsiCircuitAdjStateChanges.description: This is the number of times an adjacency off of this circuit goes from down to up or from up to down state.

wfOsiCircuitInitFailures.name: wfOsiCircuitInitFailures
wfOsiCircuitInitFailures.description: This is the number of times this circuit fails to initialize.

wfOsiCircuitRejectedAdjs.name: wfOsiCircuitRejectedAdjs
wfOsiCircuitRejectedAdjs.description: This is the number of Adjacencies that were rejected on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadLsps.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadLsps
wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadLsps.description: This is the number of bad Lsps received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadSnps.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadSnps
wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadSnps.description: This is the number of BAD Sequence Number Pdus received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadEshs.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadEshs
wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadEshs.description: This is the number of bad ESHs received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadL1Iihs.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadL1Iihs
wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadL1Iihs.description: This is the number of bad L1 IIHs received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadL2Iihs.name: wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadL2Iihs
wfOsiCircuitReceivedBadL2Iihs.description: This is the number of bad L2 IIHs received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitL1DrChanges.name: wfOsiCircuitL1DrChanges
wfOsiCircuitL1DrChanges.description: This is the number of times the L1 Designated Router has been elected on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitL2DrChanges.name: wfOsiCircuitL2DrChanges
wfOsiCircuitL2DrChanges.description: This is the number of times the L2 Designated Router has been elected on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpForwarding.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpForwarding
wfOsiCircuitClnpForwarding.description: This shows whether forwarding is enabled over this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpDefaultLifeTime.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpDefaultLifeTime
wfOsiCircuitClnpDefaultLifeTime.description: This is the lifetime included in clnp pdus generated by this router (i.e. echo and echo reply pdus, error report pdus).

wfOsiCircuitClnpInReceives.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInReceives
wfOsiCircuitClnpInReceives.description: This is the number of CLNP pdus received from this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpInAddrErrors.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInAddrErrors
wfOsiCircuitClnpInAddrErrors.description: This is the number of CLNP pdus recived from this circuit with Address format errors.

wfOsiCircuitClnpForwPdus.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpForwPdus
wfOsiCircuitClnpForwPdus.description: This is the number of Clnp PDUs received on this circuit that are forwarded.

wfOsiCircuitClnpInUnknownNlps.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInUnknownNlps
wfOsiCircuitClnpInUnknownNlps.description: This is the number of Clnp PDUs received on this circuit where the network layer addressed is unknown (Bad NLPID).

wfOsiCircuitClnpInDelivers.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInDelivers
wfOsiCircuitClnpInDelivers.description: This is the number of Clnp PDUs received on this circuit whose destination is this router.

wfOsiCircuitClnpInUnknownUlps.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInUnknownUlps
wfOsiCircuitClnpInUnknownUlps.description: This is number of Clnp PDUs received on this circuit addressed to this router where the upper layer is unknown.

wfOsiCircuitClnpSegCreates.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpSegCreates
wfOsiCircuitClnpSegCreates.description: This is the number of CLNP segments created from pdus received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpInOpts.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInOpts
wfOsiCircuitClnpInOpts.description: This is the number of CLNP pdus received with an options portion.

wfOsiCircuitClnpOutOpts.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpOutOpts
wfOsiCircuitClnpOutOpts.description: This is the number of CLNP pdus sent with an options portion.

wfOsiCircuitEsisEshIns.name: wfOsiCircuitEsisEshIns
wfOsiCircuitEsisEshIns.description: This is the number of ESHs received from this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitEsisIshOuts.name: wfOsiCircuitEsisIshOuts
wfOsiCircuitEsisIshOuts.description: This is the number of ISHs sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitEsisRduOuts.name: wfOsiCircuitEsisRduOuts
wfOsiCircuitEsisRduOuts.description: This is the number of Redirects sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitL1DesignatedRouter.name: wfOsiCircuitL1DesignatedRouter
wfOsiCircuitL1DesignatedRouter.description: This is the ID of the L1 Designated Router on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitL2DesignatedRouter.name: wfOsiCircuitL2DesignatedRouter
wfOsiCircuitL2DesignatedRouter.description: This is the ID of the L2 Designated Router on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpOutEchoReplies.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpOutEchoReplies
wfOsiCircuitClnpOutEchoReplies.description: This is the number of CLNP Echo Replies sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpOutEchoRequests.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpOutEchoRequests
wfOsiCircuitClnpOutEchoRequests.description: This is the number of Clnp Echo Requests sent out this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpInEchoReplies.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInEchoReplies
wfOsiCircuitClnpInEchoReplies.description: This is the number of CLNP Echo Replies received on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitClnpInEchoRequests.name: wfOsiCircuitClnpInEchoRequests
wfOsiCircuitClnpInEchoRequests.description: This is the number of CLNP Echo Requests recived on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitNumDynEsAdjs.name: wfOsiCircuitNumDynEsAdjs
wfOsiCircuitNumDynEsAdjs.description: This is the number of Dynamic End System Adjacencies formed on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitNumDynL1Adjs.name: wfOsiCircuitNumDynL1Adjs
wfOsiCircuitNumDynL1Adjs.description: This is the number of Dynamic Level 1 Intermediate System Adjacencies formed on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitNumDynL2Adjs.name: wfOsiCircuitNumDynL2Adjs
wfOsiCircuitNumDynL2Adjs.description: This is the number of Dynamic Level 2 Intermediate System Adjacencies formed on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitNumDynPtpIsAdjs.name: wfOsiCircuitNumDynPtpIsAdjs
wfOsiCircuitNumDynPtpIsAdjs.description: This is the number of Dynamic Intermediate System Point-to-Point Adjacencies formed on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitNumDynPtpEsAdjs.name: wfOsiCircuitNumDynPtpEsAdjs
wfOsiCircuitNumDynPtpEsAdjs.description: This is the number of Dynamic End System Point-to-Point Adjaciences formed on this circuit.

wfOsiCircuitBadIshReceived.name: wfOsiCircuitBadIshReceived
wfOsiCircuitBadIshReceived.description: This is the number of bad Intermediate System Hellos received on this circuit. These will only be received on Point-to-Point circuits.

wfOsiCircuitEsisIshIns.name: wfOsiCircuitEsisIshIns
wfOsiCircuitEsisIshIns.description: This is the number of good Intermediate System Hellos received on this circuit. These will only be received on Point-to-Point circuits.

wfOsiCircuitIihHoldMultiplier.name: wfOsiCircuitIihHoldMultiplier
wfOsiCircuitIihHoldMultiplier.description: This is the multiplier value used to compute the hold time set in the IIH PDUs transmitted from this router. Hold time equals IIH Timer times IIH Hold Multiplier.

wfOsiCircuitIshHoldMultiplier.name: wfOsiCircuitIshHoldMultiplier
wfOsiCircuitIshHoldMultiplier.description: This is the multiplier value used to compute the hold time set in the ISH PDUs transmitted from this router. Hold time equals IIH Timer times IIH Hold Multiplier.

wfOsiCircuitDisableRedirect.name: wfOsiCircuitDisableRedirect
wfOsiCircuitDisableRedirect.description: Allow Redirects to be disabled. This is required when operating over Frame Relay in group mode in a partial mesh topology.

wfOsiExternalAddressTable.name: wfOsiExternalAddressTable
wfOsiExternalAddressTable.description: This is the table of External Addresses for this Router.

wfOsiExternalAddressEntry.name: wfOsiExternalAddressEntry
wfOsiExternalAddressEntry.description: This is the External Address Record for this Router.

wfOsiExtAddrDelete.name: wfOsiExtAddrDelete
wfOsiExtAddrDelete.description: This is the Create/Delete parameter for this ExtAddr entry.

wfOsiExtAddr.name: wfOsiExtAddr
wfOsiExtAddr.description: This is the prefix external address. It is also the inst_id.

wfOsiExtAddrCircuit.name: wfOsiExtAddrCircuit
wfOsiExtAddrCircuit.description: This is the circuit to go out for this adj.

wfOsiExtAddrNibbleLength.name: wfOsiExtAddrNibbleLength
wfOsiExtAddrNibbleLength.description: This is the length in nibbles of the external address.

wfOsiExtAddrSnpa.name: wfOsiExtAddrSnpa
wfOsiExtAddrSnpa.description: This is the SNPA of the neighbor on this circuit.

wfOsiExtAddrCost.name: wfOsiExtAddrCost
wfOsiExtAddrCost.description: This is the external metric cost to this address.

wfOsiStaticEsTable.name: wfOsiStaticEsTable
wfOsiStaticEsTable.description: This is the Static ES Table for this router.

wfOsiStaticEsEntry.name: wfOsiStaticEsEntry
wfOsiStaticEsEntry.description: This is the Static ES entry for the Static ES Table.

wfOsiStaticEsDelete.name: wfOsiStaticEsDelete
wfOsiStaticEsDelete.description: This is the Create/Delete parameter for this Static ES entry.

wfOsiStaticEsDisable.name: wfOsiStaticEsDisable
wfOsiStaticEsDisable.description: Enable/Disable parameter for this Static ES.

wfOsiStaticEsId.name: wfOsiStaticEsId
wfOsiStaticEsId.description: This is the ESID of the neighbor.

wfOsiStaticEsCircuit.name: wfOsiStaticEsCircuit
wfOsiStaticEsCircuit.description: This is the circuit to go out for this adj.

wfOsiStaticEsSnpa.name: wfOsiStaticEsSnpa
wfOsiStaticEsSnpa.description: This is the SNPA of the neighbor on this circuit.

wfOsiTrafficFilterDelete.name: wfOsiTrafficFilterDelete
wfOsiTrafficFilterDelete.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfOsiTrafficFilterDisable.name: wfOsiTrafficFilterDisable
wfOsiTrafficFilterDisable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfOsiTrafficFilterStatus.name: wfOsiTrafficFilterStatus
wfOsiTrafficFilterStatus.description: Defines the current status of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfOsiTrafficFilterCounter.name: wfOsiTrafficFilterCounter
wfOsiTrafficFilterCounter.description: The number of received packets that have matched this rule.

wfOsiTrafficFilterCircuit.name: wfOsiTrafficFilterCircuit
wfOsiTrafficFilterCircuit.description: The ID of the Circuit to which the filter is applied.

wfOsiL1LspHdrTable.name: wfOsiL1LspHdrTable
wfOsiL1LspHdrTable.description: 2 u_int32's so the inst_id len is 2.

wfOsiL1LspHdrEntry.name: wfOsiL1LspHdrEntry
wfOsiL1LspHdrEntry.description: A Record in the Level 1 Lsp Header Table

wfOsiL1LspHdrLspId.name: wfOsiL1LspHdrLspId
wfOsiL1LspHdrLspId.description: LSPID = Source ID + Pseudo-node ID + LSP number

wfOsiL2LspHdrTable.name: wfOsiL2LspHdrTable
wfOsiL2LspHdrTable.description: 2 u_int32's so the inst_id len is 2.

wfOsiL2LspHdrEntry.name: wfOsiL2LspHdrEntry
wfOsiL2LspHdrEntry.description: A Record in the Lsp Header Table

wfOsiL2LspHdrLspId.name: wfOsiL2LspHdrLspId
wfOsiL2LspHdrLspId.description: LSPID = Source ID + Pseudo-node ID + LSP number

wfOsiDynAdjEntry.name: wfOsiDynAdjEntry
wfOsiDynAdjEntry.description: Adjacency Table - the real index is the adjacency id

wfOsiDynAdjDatabase.name: wfOsiDynAdjDatabase
wfOsiDynAdjDatabase.description: Database into which the Adjacency is stored, 1=ES, 2=Level 1 IS, 3=Level 2 IS.

wfOsiDynAdjState.name: wfOsiDynAdjState
wfOsiDynAdjState.description: The state of the adjacency. INITIALIZING, UP or FAILED

wfOsiDynAdjCircuitId.name: wfOsiDynAdjCircuitId
wfOsiDynAdjCircuitId.description: A unique value for each known circuit.

wfOsiDynAdjPriority.name: wfOsiDynAdjPriority
wfOsiDynAdjPriority.description: Priority to become designated router. IS only.

wfOsiDynAdjLanId.name: wfOsiDynAdjLanId
wfOsiDynAdjLanId.description: LAN ID from Designated Router. IS only.

wfOsiL1RoutesTable.name: wfOsiL1RoutesTable
wfOsiL1RoutesTable.description: This is the L1 Routes Table for this router.

wfOsiL1RouteEntry.name: wfOsiL1RouteEntry
wfOsiL1RouteEntry.description: This is the L1 Route entry for the Routes Table.

wfOsiL1RouteId.name: wfOsiL1RouteId
